title.narrative: COMMUNICATIONS AND PUBLIC ADVOCACY

description.narrative: UNICEF Cambodia staff and partners are provided the guidance, tools and resources to effectively communicate, advocate and develop partnerships regarding child rights issues with stakeholders., which contributes to Cross-Sectoral Communication For Development, Cross-Sectoral Communication For Development (Covid), Cross-Sectoral Monitoring, Data And Situation Analyses, Other Cross-Sectoral Programme Areas. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: The Cambodia country programme is efficiently designed, coordinated, managed and supported to meet quality results-based management standards and achieve results for children.

description.narrative: Effective risk communication and community engagement initiatives are implemented to contain the spread of the COVID-19, ensuring that the entire population, especially the most marginalized, women and children, have access to reliable and tailored information on the risks of COVID-19. Cross-cutting messages and innovative communication approaches are developed to raise awareness on the pandemic's multi-dimensional impact on children and advocate for resumption and continuity of services. Daily communication support is provided to all UNICEF sections, government and development partners. On-going efforts are undertaken to position UNICEF as a knowledge leader and advocate for children through offline and on-line advocacy. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:21/08/2020
